WEBVTT

00:00.600 --> 00:03.402
[previously on childrens
hospital...]

00:07.273 --> 00:11.076
Hey, dori, toss me the keys
to recovery room 6a.

00:12.412 --> 00:15.381
You see, dori, rather than
go on a trip somewhere

00:15.383 --> 00:17.016
Unfamiliar and expensive,

00:17.018 --> 00:20.319
I've decided to go somewhere
less unfamiliar

00:20.321 --> 00:21.854
And non-expensive --

00:21.856 --> 00:23.188
Right here
at the hospital.

00:23.190 --> 00:26.091
So instead of a va-cation,
you're doing a...

00:26.093 --> 00:28.327
Staycation.
...Poor person's vacation,
right.

00:28.329 --> 00:29.962
[ mid-tempo music plays ]

00:34.434 --> 00:35.701
Juice it up to 30cc.

00:35.703 --> 00:37.102
Jimmy, give me two fingers
on the artery.

00:37.104 --> 00:39.405
Black guy, I need a millimeter
on the compressor.

00:39.407 --> 00:41.106
I'd learn your name
if it made a difference.

00:41.108 --> 00:42.241
Beth, where's the kidney?

00:42.243 --> 00:43.442
It didn't make it
here in time.

00:43.444 --> 00:44.410
There's nothing we can do.

00:44.412 --> 00:45.577
Oh, yeah?

00:45.579 --> 00:47.413
How 'bout we do "saving
this little girl's life"?

00:49.149 --> 00:50.549
[ chuckles ]

00:50.551 --> 00:52.684
Whoo! Whoo!

00:52.686 --> 00:53.986
Beep! Beep!
[ laughs ]

00:53.988 --> 00:57.322
[ imitates a guitar solo ]

00:57.324 --> 00:58.424
I bike!

00:58.426 --> 00:59.525
What's up, pedestrian?

00:59.527 --> 01:02.061
I just had a pretty
intense bike ride.

01:02.063 --> 01:04.629
Hey, what's up, owen?

01:04.632 --> 01:05.764
How's it going?

01:05.766 --> 01:07.366
You, uh --
do you ride or what?

01:07.368 --> 01:08.534
Do I ride?

01:08.536 --> 01:09.568
Yeah.

01:09.570 --> 01:10.702
Yeah, I ride.

01:10.704 --> 01:12.171
I live to ride

01:12.173 --> 01:15.474
And I ride to live,
so, yeah.

01:15.476 --> 01:17.076
Well, cool, man.

01:17.078 --> 01:20.479
Cool. We should, uh, you know,
cut some pavement together.

01:20.481 --> 01:25.317
Whatevs, just two dudes
riding around as friends.

01:25.319 --> 01:26.118
[ laughs ]

01:26.120 --> 01:27.619
So funny.
"friends."

01:27.621 --> 01:28.921
Oh.

01:28.923 --> 01:30.189
But if you were serious,

01:30.191 --> 01:33.225
Then I suggest you
ditch the unicycle

01:33.227 --> 01:36.228
And get yourself
a two-cycle.

01:36.863 --> 01:39.298
I'm talking about
a [bleep] bike!

01:39.300 --> 01:40.566
[ laughter ]

01:40.568 --> 01:41.967
Nurse beth:
And then he sewed him up.

01:41.969 --> 01:43.535
[ laughter ]

01:43.537 --> 01:44.937
Oh, dr. Richie,

01:44.939 --> 01:47.272
You are truly this hospital's
rock star surgeon.

01:47.274 --> 01:49.208
Hey, man, I didn't say it.
<i>The times</i> did.

01:49.210 --> 01:52.144
So, dr. Richie,
any plans this weekend?

01:52.146 --> 01:54.980
Oh, well,
it's my birthday tomorrow.

01:54.982 --> 01:58.984
So, I'm gonna be f--
my god, 27 years old.

01:58.986 --> 02:00.285
Be careful, okay.

02:00.287 --> 02:02.488
I'm mean all the great
rock stars died at 27 --

02:02.490 --> 02:05.891
Jimi hendrix, janis joplin,
kurt cobain, jim morrison.

02:05.893 --> 02:08.460
Well, there's got to be some
rock stars who live past 27.

02:08.461 --> 02:10.696
I mean, what about
amy winehouse, brian jones,

02:10.698 --> 02:11.830
Blues legend robert johnson?

02:11.832 --> 02:12.831
Nope.

02:12.833 --> 02:14.199
How about ron "pigpen" mckernan,

02:14.201 --> 02:16.335
Founding keyboardist
of the grateful dead?

02:16.337 --> 02:17.503
Not pigpen?

02:17.505 --> 02:18.804
Oh, no.

02:18.806 --> 02:19.838
Mph!

02:19.840 --> 02:21.140
I can't die tomorrow.

02:21.142 --> 02:22.674
I have my whole two-thirds
of my whole life

02:22.676 --> 02:23.809
Left ahead of me.

02:23.811 --> 02:24.676
[ sighs ]

02:24.678 --> 02:26.078
Okay, here's an idea --

02:26.080 --> 02:28.614
You know how if you
never fall asleep,

02:28.616 --> 02:30.048
The days don't change?

02:30.050 --> 02:32.518
I was born almost 27 years ago,
not yesterday.

02:32.520 --> 02:33.619
Of course I know that.

02:33.621 --> 02:35.020
Right, right.

02:35.022 --> 02:38.457
So, as long as you stay awake,
you'll never turn 27.

02:38.459 --> 02:40.058
I got to stay awake.

02:40.060 --> 02:41.493
What am I gonna do?

02:41.495 --> 02:44.263
Whenever I have to do
a triple shift,

02:44.265 --> 02:47.199
I stay awake by taking
high doses of amphetamine pills.

02:47.201 --> 02:48.834
Yeah, but don't you need
a psychiatrist

02:48.836 --> 02:50.068
To prescribe
that type of thing?

02:50.070 --> 02:52.271
A psychiatrist
or a certain paramedic.

02:52.273 --> 02:54.072
Okay, okay.
I'm listening.

02:54.074 --> 02:55.774
I can give you pills.

02:55.776 --> 02:57.709
Here.

02:57.711 --> 03:00.746
I'm with you so far.
Go on.

03:00.748 --> 03:03.248
That's it.
That's your answer.

03:03.250 --> 03:06.485
Might I order up a round
of your famous cottage cheese,

03:06.487 --> 03:08.453
A side of jello shots,

03:08.455 --> 03:11.523
And a small orange juice
from concentrate.

03:11.525 --> 03:14.660
I'm on staycation!
Calories be damned!

03:14.662 --> 03:16.929
[ chuckles ]

03:16.931 --> 03:20.165
[ breathes deeply ]

03:20.167 --> 03:21.533
Are you as bored as I am?

03:21.535 --> 03:22.568
Excuse me?

03:22.570 --> 03:24.102
I-I-I'm not very good

03:24.104 --> 03:25.437
At introductions.

03:25.439 --> 03:27.673
At least that's what
my wife rita used to say

03:27.675 --> 03:28.907
Before she passed away.

03:28.909 --> 03:31.743
So, here goes nothin' --
don crawfield.

03:31.745 --> 03:35.380
Uh, lieutenant donald crawfield,
1st battalion,

03:35.382 --> 03:37.849
7th marine regiment,
uh, vietnam,

03:37.851 --> 03:38.917
In case you're
keeping score.

03:38.919 --> 03:40.586
Timmy: Grandpa?

03:40.588 --> 03:45.157
I'm right here, timmy, just, uh,
talking with a beautiful lady.

03:45.159 --> 03:46.658
Look [sighs] don...

03:46.660 --> 03:50.162
I see what you're doing here,
and I'll let you down easy.

03:50.164 --> 03:55.033
I came here to get away
from it all -- by myself.

03:55.035 --> 03:56.935
Message received, ma'am.

03:56.937 --> 03:58.303
Oh, don?

03:58.305 --> 03:59.271
Uh...

03:59.273 --> 04:00.973
I'm sorry about
your wife...

04:00.975 --> 04:02.374
And about vietnam.

04:02.376 --> 04:05.244
That -- that was
a real boondoggle.

04:06.779 --> 04:09.114
Hi. Um, excuse me.

04:09.116 --> 04:12.618
Do you guys sell bicycles
with two wheels here?

04:12.620 --> 04:14.319
Thank you.

04:14.321 --> 04:16.887
Oh!

04:16.890 --> 04:19.423
Yo, brotha, whasuup?

04:19.426 --> 04:21.392
Looking for
a fiberglass horse.

04:21.394 --> 04:22.728
What are
those guys doing?

04:22.730 --> 04:24.896
That's called getting serious
about cycling.

04:24.898 --> 04:27.332
Another thing it's called
is "getting serious about
shooting steroids in your butt

04:27.334 --> 04:29.167
So you can get better
at cycling."

04:29.169 --> 04:31.803
That's a real mouthful.
That's why we don't
say it that much.

04:31.805 --> 04:33.171
I'm just looking
for a bike.

04:33.173 --> 04:36.808
Oh, look who decided
to show up.

04:36.810 --> 04:38.210
Yeah.

04:38.212 --> 04:40.579
All right, blake.
I guess you are the real deal.

04:40.581 --> 04:41.747
[ scoffs ]

04:41.749 --> 04:43.115
You ready to get serious...

04:43.117 --> 04:44.583
About cycling?

04:44.585 --> 04:46.218
[ nervously ] yes.

04:46.220 --> 04:49.388
[ "bap u" by party favor plays ]

04:51.624 --> 04:54.026
[ grunts ]

04:54.028 --> 04:55.093
[ farts ]

04:55.095 --> 04:57.329
Whoo! Oh!

04:58.064 --> 04:58.864
Come on!

04:58.866 --> 05:00.432
[ grunts ]

05:04.504 --> 05:06.672
Ha! Oh!

05:08.941 --> 05:10.509
[ stapler clicking ]

05:13.179 --> 05:15.113
Knock, knock.
Who's there?

05:15.115 --> 05:17.582
I made that sound because
it's a curtain.

05:17.584 --> 05:18.984
Timmy's asleep.

05:18.986 --> 05:20.886
I thought I'd go
take a walk,

05:20.888 --> 05:22.688
Maybe visit
your gift shop.

05:22.690 --> 05:24.556
Could use a wingman.

05:24.558 --> 05:26.425
Fine,

05:26.427 --> 05:29.061
But only because
they let me suck the helium

05:29.063 --> 05:31.096
From the balloon tanks there.

05:31.098 --> 05:33.098
[ birds chirping ]

05:33.100 --> 05:35.367
Ah, here's a good one.
[ chuckling ] yeah.

05:35.369 --> 05:37.202
"hoping you
get well soon...

05:37.204 --> 05:39.304
Because we're all sick
of waiting."

05:39.306 --> 05:41.740
[ high-pitched voice ]
now that is right on the edge

05:41.742 --> 05:43.141
Of "just wrong."

05:43.143 --> 05:46.345
Dark chocolate, 72%.
You ever tried this?

05:46.347 --> 05:48.046
[ normal voice ]
I'm not insane.

05:48.048 --> 05:49.314
I never go above 50%.

05:49.316 --> 05:52.918
Then again, I --
I am on staycation.

05:52.920 --> 05:55.120
Take a bite of this.

05:58.524 --> 05:59.858
Me likey.

05:59.860 --> 06:00.892
You are so bad.

06:00.894 --> 06:02.494
You think that's bad?

06:03.663 --> 06:05.464
[ laughs ]

06:05.466 --> 06:08.900
[ laughing ] yeah, man.
I can breath fire!

06:08.902 --> 06:10.736
I can breath fire, bro!

06:10.738 --> 06:12.237
Yeah.

06:13.840 --> 06:15.040
No.

06:15.042 --> 06:16.575
Let's clip 'em in
and do it up.

06:16.577 --> 06:17.476
Clip 'em in.

06:17.478 --> 06:19.711
Rippinin' it
and clippinin' it.

06:19.713 --> 06:20.746
[ shakily ] whoa.

06:20.748 --> 06:23.882
Yeah! Done.
Bring in the next one!

06:23.884 --> 06:25.183
Let's go!

06:25.185 --> 06:27.519
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
There is nobody left.

06:27.521 --> 06:29.855
Hey, when did this happen?

06:29.857 --> 06:31.523
Hours ago. Glenn,

06:31.525 --> 06:33.692
This is your
48th surgery today.

06:33.694 --> 06:34.693
[ laughs ]

06:34.695 --> 06:35.827
Maybe you should sleep.

06:38.865 --> 06:40.832
I'll sleep when I'm dead.

06:40.834 --> 06:44.703
[ slow tempo music plays ]

06:46.939 --> 06:51.376
You're different from
the kinds of girls I'm used to.

06:51.378 --> 06:54.079
Maybe you haven't met
that many girls with...

06:54.081 --> 06:57.115
Amyotrophic
lateral sclerosis.

06:57.117 --> 07:01.920
♪ my anxious heart has seen ♪

07:01.922 --> 07:05.056
Grrr! Grrr!

07:05.058 --> 07:07.893
Grrr! Two days
in a row!

07:07.895 --> 07:08.860
Yeah.

07:08.862 --> 07:09.961
Oh! Oh!

07:09.963 --> 07:13.131
Oh. [ grunts ]

07:13.133 --> 07:15.233
Oh, shoot!

07:15.235 --> 07:17.202
I got to get more serious.

07:17.204 --> 07:19.638
Ah. Oh.

07:19.640 --> 07:20.405
[ groans ]

07:20.407 --> 07:22.207
Blake, take it easy, man.

07:22.209 --> 07:25.143
[ grunts ]
I am so serious!

07:25.145 --> 07:26.845
What are you
talking about?

07:26.847 --> 07:27.879
[ grunting ]

07:27.881 --> 07:29.047
All right, man.

07:29.049 --> 07:29.981
Don't do that.

07:29.983 --> 07:31.716
No, come on, man!

07:31.718 --> 07:33.785
It's $5,000 bike!

07:33.787 --> 07:35.720
Bike! [ grunts ]

07:35.722 --> 07:38.790
What the hell is wrong
with you, blake?!

07:38.792 --> 07:39.758
What?!

07:39.760 --> 07:40.859
You trashed my bike!

07:40.861 --> 07:43.428
It doesn't matter, bro!
We're friends.

07:43.430 --> 07:46.298
You're out of control!
We're not friends!

07:46.300 --> 07:48.567
Let's go, guys.

07:48.569 --> 07:49.401
Owen!

07:49.403 --> 07:51.770
Bro-wen!
I do this for you.

07:51.772 --> 07:54.573
Look how hard-core I am!

07:57.376 --> 07:58.944
Glenn!
Never sleep.

07:58.946 --> 08:00.979
Glenn,
what are you doing?!

08:01.781 --> 08:04.449
[ crying ] you don't know
what it's like to be me.

08:04.451 --> 08:06.318
You don't know!

08:06.320 --> 08:09.754
You sit there in
your fancy dress...

08:09.756 --> 08:11.723
These are scrubs
and I'm standing.

08:11.725 --> 08:13.692
And you judge me?!

08:13.694 --> 08:15.560
I'm a rock star!

08:15.562 --> 08:19.564
I can eat more chicken
than any man alive.

08:19.566 --> 08:21.466
Mm.

08:23.836 --> 08:27.239
[ sighs, chuckles ]

08:29.242 --> 08:31.776
[ gasps ]

08:31.778 --> 08:33.945
More.

08:33.947 --> 08:36.914
[ gasping ]

08:36.917 --> 08:38.049
What? Oh, hey.

08:38.051 --> 08:39.017
Chief,

08:39.019 --> 08:40.485
I'd like you
to meet --

08:40.486 --> 08:42.486
Where's the chocolate?
I-I-I need some chocolate.

08:42.489 --> 08:43.655
Maybe later, chief --

08:43.657 --> 08:44.389
No!

08:44.391 --> 08:45.657
If I wanted it later,

08:45.659 --> 08:47.826
I would have asked
for it later!

08:47.828 --> 08:49.027
Wouldn't I?!

08:49.029 --> 08:50.529
I'm sorry, baby.

08:50.531 --> 08:52.163
I just got
a little crazy there.

08:52.165 --> 08:53.732
On her death bed,
my wife said,

08:53.734 --> 08:54.966
"find someone new."

08:54.968 --> 08:58.603
But no other woman ever
compared until I met you.

08:58.605 --> 09:00.438
It's not about us anymore,
though, is it?

09:00.440 --> 09:01.840
It's about the chocolate.

09:01.842 --> 09:06.077
Don't get all dramatic.
Just give me the chocolate!

09:06.079 --> 09:07.279
Oh, my god.

09:07.281 --> 09:08.914
Nice to have met you,
chief.

09:10.950 --> 09:12.684
[ grunting, screaming ]

09:13.653 --> 09:17.188
[ groans ]
I need one more squirt.

09:17.190 --> 09:19.291
Oh, rock and roll!

09:19.293 --> 09:20.759
I'll never sleep!

09:20.761 --> 09:21.860
Aah!

09:23.329 --> 09:24.529
Oh, hey.

09:24.531 --> 09:26.131
You got your chocolate

09:26.133 --> 09:27.365
In my amphetamine.

09:27.367 --> 09:29.734
You got your steroids
on my chocolate.

09:29.736 --> 09:32.504
You got your amphetamines
in my steroids.

09:35.207 --> 09:36.942
T-that's pretty good.

09:36.944 --> 09:38.043
Huh?

09:38.045 --> 09:39.744
Oh!

09:39.746 --> 09:40.812
Oh!

09:40.814 --> 09:43.048
[ screams ]

09:43.050 --> 09:44.983
What do you know!

09:44.985 --> 09:47.052
Hey!
Wait a minute...

09:47.054 --> 09:52.490
Did we accidentally discover
a miraculous new compound?!

09:52.492 --> 09:54.426
[ all cheering, laughter ]

09:57.396 --> 09:59.731
Ah, the restorative properties
are flawless.

09:59.733 --> 10:01.499
No discernible
side effects.

10:01.501 --> 10:03.201
Fellas, I say we got
a new drug.

10:03.203 --> 10:05.804
With apologies
and a tip of the proverbial hat

10:05.806 --> 10:07.238
To one huey lewis,
of course.

10:07.240 --> 10:08.406
Yes!

10:14.313 --> 10:15.880
<i>Sal: Attention, staff --</i>

10:15.882 --> 10:18.383
<i>Congratulations to</i>
<i>the three new co-presidents</i>

10:18.385 --> 10:19.584
<i>Of childrens hospital.</i>

10:19.586 --> 10:21.987
[ "psychic kids"
by we are wolves plays ]

10:29.261 --> 10:30.862
Ah.
Oh.

10:30.864 --> 10:32.230
Oh.
Oh.

10:32.232 --> 10:33.098
Oh.

10:33.100 --> 10:34.766
[ laughs ]

10:34.768 --> 10:35.767
Whee!

10:35.769 --> 10:37.235
[ laughs ]

10:37.237 --> 10:38.103
Oh!

10:38.105 --> 10:40.839
[ laughing ] hey.

10:40.841 --> 10:41.940
We're flying!

10:41.942 --> 10:43.375
We're higher than god!

10:43.377 --> 10:44.542
Yeah!

10:49.582 --> 10:52.884
[ slurring ]
that is some intense shit.

10:52.886 --> 10:53.685
[ groans ]

10:53.687 --> 10:55.687
[ mid-tempo music plays ]

10:55.689 --> 10:57.789
Excuse me.
Sorry, guys.

10:57.791 --> 10:59.991
Um, dr. Richie,
I double-checked.

10:59.993 --> 11:02.560
Uh, it turns out that
rock stars die at 27,

11:02.562 --> 11:04.696
But rock star surgeons
die at 45.

11:04.698 --> 11:06.931
So you got a couple
of decades left, plus.
